      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARABOLE RICO (1) was well fancied last time on the strength of the win two back but could only manage third (31.37) at Gawler. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from six starts. Winning claims. PAW EVA (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when eighth at Murray Bridge over 455m behind Destroying (26.39) in a OPEN. Placed at her previous run. Comes out of a hot form race last start. A big run wouldn't surprise. FEDERAL LADY (7) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, 1.75 lengths from the winner Paw Leon (17.08) at this track. Racing well and deserves a win. FENCER MAX (8) is building a nice sequence of placings and is sure to play a big role again.",
